The electrochemical performances of NiSe2/Ni(OH)2-2h//PPD-rGO asymmetric supercapacitor are presented in Figs. 5b–f and S12. Calculated from the GCD curves of NiSe2/Ni(OH)2-2h//PPD-rGO, at a current density of 1 A g−1, an ultrahigh specific capacity of 302 C g−1 (189 F g−1) can be obtained. Furthermore, almost 100% coulomb efficiencies were acquired at different current densities (Fig. 5d). The energy density and power density can be acquired using Eqs. 7 and 8, and the results are shown in Fig. 5e [51]:7E=Im∫t1t2Vdt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
